import React,{useState} from 'react' export const User = () => { const [user, setUser] = useState({ name : "", email : "", password : "", address : "", city : "", state : "", zipcode : "", isChecked : false }) let handleSubmit = async(event)=>{ event.preventDefault(); } let handleChange = (event) =>{ let newData = {} setUser(event.target.value) if(event.target.name =='isChecked'){ console.log('----->',event.target.checked) newData[event.target.name] = event.target.checked; }else{ newData[event.target.name] = event.target.value; } let userData = {...user,...newData} setUser(userData) } return (
{JSON.stringify(user)}
) }
